RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 76. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LORD OF LIGHT took back off of the early pace while never far back, angled four wide nearing the top of the lane, closed well heading to mid-stretch, responded to steady urging while on the left lead in the final sixteenth, drew to even terms with SGT POWELL in deep stretch and kept to task in the final strides to prevail. SGT POWELL showed early speed and established the lead heading into the first turn, set moderate fractions while prompted through the backstretch run, maintained a narrow lead to the quarter marker, battled for the lead with LOKI OF ASGARD to mid-stretch, was confronted by LORD OF LIGHT nearing the sixteenth-marker, was outfinished by that rival in deep stretch and just held for second at the finish. LOKI OF ASGARD was forwardly placed into the first turn, kept close attendance to the pacesetter through the backstretch run, remained close to the pace to the quarter marker, battled for the lead with SGT POWELL to mid-stretch, was not able to match strides with the top pair in deep stretch and just missed for second, while holding for third. DO IT FOR DAVE was allowed to settle in the early running, was asked for run while widest heading into the stretch, mounted a five wide bid into the drive, was gaining in the final furlong and just missed for third. MICKEY GOLDMILL was unhurried in the early stages, saved ground to the second turn, advanced in the stretch run but could not muster the needed late response. G'S LAST CHANCE stalked the moderate pace, came within aim while three wide on the second turn, ran evenly to mid-stretch and lacked a late rally. EASTER COMMAND settled off of the early pace while not far back, maintained position through the backstretch run while outside of rivals, raced four wide into the far turn, could not keep pace heading into the stretch and tired.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 92. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since February 1 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered when determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TALBOT BAY got off to a good start, saved ground on the rail and raced in mid-pack through the early stages, awaited room on the turn while well in hand, got a clear path turning for home, looked to tip out around LUCKY LAD near the eighth pole then surged through an opening on the rail when that one drifted out a bit and was up in time. LUCKY LAD broke well then took command of the early pace under a bit of a hold, led the field to the stretch, responded when roused and repelled all challengers save for the winner. LOOKIN TO EXCEL brushed with SHARONA'S WILD BOY after the break, tracked the pacesetter to the stretch, tipped out to the two path and ran on well down the late but was unable to get past a stubborn LUCKY LAD. SHARONA'S WILD BOY broke out at the start and brushed slightly with LOOKIN TO EXCEL, then overcorrected in the other direction and caused INDULGE to alter path, gathered up then raced with the early leaders, lost some ground in the turn then re-rallied, was still with a chance when behind horses in deep stretch, tipped out and found room but was much too late. INDULGE was bothered after the start when SHARONA'S WILD BOY veered into his path and then forced him into TALBOT BAY, fell back and chased the field to the turn, attempted to rally three wide and managed to pass a couple in the final furlong. IDIOT'S GOLD broke well and was up close in the early running, steadied slightly just past the nine-sixteenths pole, made a three wide bid on the turn and loomed a threat at the top of the stretch but was outfinished in the late stages. COUNT ASHER outrun for the first quarter mile, began to make some forward progress through the turn, came under heavy pressure approaching the five-sixteenths pole and was unable to improve position from there. TOLONISITO away well, was close up early, came under a ride near the seven-sixteenths pole, stopped passing the three-eighths marker, was eased through the stretch and walked off under his own power.
